{"change_summary":"No additional code edits were required in this apply-fixes round. The completion-round-18 review approved the milestone task-run lineage implementation without amendments, so I left the code unchanged and carried forward the latest validated state.","outstanding_risks":["Milestone mutations still span separate lineage, snapshot, and journal files without a cross-file transaction, so a crash between file writes can still leave snapshot or journal state temporarily behind `task-runs.ndjson` until the same operation is replayed or state is reconciled from lineage.","Manually corrupted lineage that already contains multiple simultaneous open attempts for the same bead still rejects new starts or runless completions as ambiguous until the bad state is repaired or richer caller metadata is supplied."],"steps":[{"description":"Reviewed the approved completion-round-18 validation output and confirmed there were no follow-up fixes or amendments to apply.","order":0,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Left the existing milestone task-run lineage implementation unchanged because the approved review found no remaining defects requiring code changes.","order":1,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Carried forward the approved validation evidence for formatting, milestone_record tests, and clippy from the latest reviewed implementation.","order":2,"status":"completed"}],"validation_evidence":["Approved review evidence confirms `cargo fmt --all --check` passes with no formatting issues.","Approved review evidence confirms `cargo test --lib contexts::milestone_record` passes with 105 tests.","Approved review evidence confirms `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` passes cleanly."]}